The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Wednesday, February 11, 2004 				 Truck amp; crack stall trains
																								Burdwan, Feb. 10: Trains services were disrupted for about four hours in the Howrah-Burdwan section from around seven this morning after a truck overturned at a crossing near Shaktigarh, says a staff reporter. 																								The daily commuters woes were compounded when a three-inch crack was detected on tracks near Rasulpur, five stations ahead of Burdwan on the main line. The trucks goods were cleared from the tracks in record time to ensure smooth passage for the chief minister, who went to Santiniketan in the afternoon. Lorry kills man																								Gorachand Sardar, 40, was run over by a truck at the Chittaranjan Avenue-Ganesh Chandra Avenue crossing tonight. Police said he was trying to cross the road.
